{{Infobox company | name = PricePanda Group GmbH | logo = PricePanda Logo.jpg | type = [[Private company|Private]] | founded = 2012 | location = [[Berlin]], [[Germany]] (Headquarters); [[Singapore]] | key_people = Christian Schiller (Co-Founder) Louis Iskandar (Co-Founder) Philip Wegener (Managing Director) | industry = [[Internet Services]] Comparison Shopping Distributed Content Commerce | homepage = [http://www.pricepanda.com/ www.pricepanda.com] }}
'''PricePanda''' is a price [[comparison shopping website]] and [[distributed content store]], founded in 2012 by Christian Schiller and Louis Iskandar in Berlin. The managing director is Philip Wegener.{{citation needed|date=January 2017}}
==Operations== PricePanda operates in its markets by establishing business partnerships with merchants and retailers to provide information and price lists on a wide range of products. As of November 2014, the website’s database holds over 50,000 products and 100,000 prices for users to compare. Its product categories include [[cameras]], [[computers]], [[televisions]], [[video]], [[Sound|audio]], [[software]], [[smartphones]], [[entertainment]], [[navigation]], [[fashion]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pricepanda.com.ph/page/philippines-launches-fashion/|title=PricePanda Philippines Launches Fashion!|author=PricePanda|date=2014-06-16|accessdate=2014-11-13}}</ref> [[health]] and [[beauty]]. The site serves as the data source for price comparisons of shopping [[websites]].
==History== PricePanda was launched in 2012. Today the business is present in nine countries in [[Southeast Asia]], [[South Asia]] and [[Latin America]]: Year 2012 - Singapore,Indonesia and Malaysia,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://e27.co/rocket-internet-brings-price-comparison-to-singapore-and-malaysia-with-its-new-venture-pricepanda/|title=PricePanda bring price comparison to Singapore and Malaysia|author=e27|date=2012-09-20|accessdate=2014-11-13}}</ref> Year 2013 - Mexico and Philippines<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zdnet.com/more-sea-shoppers-comparing-prices-via-mobile-7000023182/|title=More SEA shoppers comparing price via mobile|author=zdnet|date=2013-11-18|accessdate=2014-11-13}}</ref> Year 2014 - Colombia and Argentina,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bogotafreeplanet.com/index.php/article/12364/|title=Argentina and Colombia follow PricePanda’s successful launch in Mexico|author=bogotafreeplanet|date=2014-02-05|accessdate=2014-11-13}}</ref> Thailand,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://e27.co/rocket-internet-backed-pricepanda-launches-services-in-thailand/|title=Rocket Internet-backed PricePanda launches servers in Thailand|author=e27|date=2014-03-26|accessdate=2014-11-13}}</ref> and India.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tropicalpost.com/rocket-internet-backed-pricepanda-launches-india-operations/|title=Rocket Internet backed PricePanda launches India operations|author=tropicalpost|date=2014-03-08|accessdate=2014-11-13}}</ref> In January 2014 PricePanda had redirected 1 million users to partners’ shops since the company’s launch in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://e27.co/rocket-internet-backed-pricepanda-directs-1m-people-partners-shops/|title=Rocket Internet-backed PricePanda directs 1M people to partners’ chops|author=e27|date=2014-01-17|accessdate=2014-11-13}}</ref>
==Mobile==
PricePanda is also optimised for mobile: as of October 2014, 44% of total visitors come from smartphones and 9% - from tablets.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.pricepanda.com.my/online-shopping-trends-2014/|title=Online Shopping Trends in 2014|author=PricePanda|date=2014-10-29|accessdate=2014-11-13}}</ref> In October 2013, the company launched its first mobile application for the [[Philippines]], [[Malaysia]], [[Singapore]] and [[Indonesia]] to enforce [[M-commerce]] in [[South East Asia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wirelessduniya.com/2013/11/08/pricepanda-releases-iphone-app-to-enforce-m-commerce-in-sea/|title=PricePanda releases iPhone App to enforce M-Commerce in SEA|author=wirelessduniya|date=2013-11-08|accessdate=2014-11-13}}</ref> The app enables users to search for a product by its name and locate prices for thousands of products in order to find the best deals online and on the go. It also enables users to visit and contact merchants' and retailers' websites within the app.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://evigo.com/pricepanda-launches-new-android-app-southeast-asian-markets/|title=PricePanda launches a new Android app for southeast Asian markets|author=Grzegorz Pawłowski|date=2013-10-03|accessdate=2014-11-13}}</ref> The mobile application is available on both [[iOS]] and [[Android (operating system)]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.techinasia.com/pricepanda-compare-prices-android-devices/|title=PricePanda now lets you compare prices through Android devices |author=TechinAsia|date=2013-10-03|accessdate=2014-11-13}}</ref>
== Investments ==
In January 2014 PricePanda raised $3 million in funding from the large German retailer [[Tengelmann Group]]. According to the company the new funding will be used to expand the business in several other markets worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://techcrunch.com/2014/01/26/pricepanda-raises-3m-from-german-retail-group-tengelmann/|title=PricePanda Raises $3M From German Retail Group Tengelmann|author=TechCrunch|date=2014-01-26|accessdate=2014-11-13}}</ref>
