'''Rádio – Top 100''' (originally '''Rádio Top 100 Oficiálna''') is the [[Slovakia|Slovak]] national airplay chart published  by the [[IFPI Czech Republic]] on a weekly basis since the cancellation of the Slovak national section ([[SNS IFPI]]) on December 31, 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kultura.pravda.sk/zabudnite-na-aurela-slovenska-ifpi-konci-ffq-/sk_khudba.asp?c=A100418_145945_sk_khudba_p46|title=Forget About Aurel: The Slovak IFPI Is Finishing|first=Matúš|last=Kvasnička|date=2010-04-19|work=[[Pravda (Slovakia)|PRAVDA]]|at=kultura.pravda.sk|publisher=PEREX|accessdate=2011-04-20|language=sk}}</ref> 
Besides the Top 100 [[record chart]], also the component '''Rádio Top 50''' is effective, featuring exclusively song releases by Slovak and/or [[Czech Republic|Czech]] artists. Online versions of the charts are released at ifpicr.cz/hitparadask, featuring Top 100, respectively Top 50 positions.

